---
import CaseStudyLayout from '../layouts/CaseStudyLayout.astro';
import Figure from '../components/Figure.astro';

const metadata = [
  { label: 'Platform', values: ['Mobile'] },
  { label: 'Roles', values: ['Visual Design', 'Motion Design'] }
];

const metrics = [
  { value: '20%', label: 'Increase in social shares YoY' },
  { value: '250k+', label: 'Total views' },
  { value: '8%', label: 'Increase in class bookings YoY' }
];
---

<CaseStudyLayout
  title="Mariana Tek Year In Motion"
  description="A personalised end-of-year recap that highlights users' fitness journey."
  heroImageSrc="/images/yearinmotion_hero.webp"
  heroImageAlt="Case Study Two Hero"
  metadata={metadata}
  metrics={metrics}
>
  <!-- Text block -->
  <div class="content-block-text">
    <p>As a Product Designer at Mariana Tek, I had the opportunity to design the company's annual Year in Motion feature, a favorite among our boutique fitness clients and their customers. For the first time at the company, I introduced animations to create a more immersive experience in the mobile app.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Offset right image -->
  <div class="content-block-offset-right">
    <Figure
      src="/images/yearinmotion_barrys.png"
      alt="Year in Motion Barry's screens"
      caption="Intro animation, top instructor stat, and final summary stat screens for Barry's."
    />
  </div>

  <!-- Text block -->
  <div class="content-block-text">
    <p>Year in Motion transforms a year of workouts into a story users can see, revisit, and share. Inspired by the delight of annual recap experiences, the goal was to make members feel recognized for their consistency, milestones, and relationship with their studio.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Two-column layout: small left, large right -->
  <div class="content-block-2col">
    <Figure
      src="/images/yearinmotion_persona-cards.webp"
      alt="Year in Motion persona cards"
      caption="Illustrated persona cards are assigned to each user based on the day and time they most often took classes."
    />
  </div>

  <!-- Text block -->
  <div class="content-block-text">
    <p>To make the experience feel more immersive, I introduced motion as a core part of the storytelling. Animated transitions, paced stat reveals, and bold visual moments helped the recap feel less like a report and more like a celebration of progress.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Full width videos grid -->
  <div class="content-block-full">
    <div class="content-block-videos-grid">
      <Figure
        videoSrc="/videos/yearinmotion_intro.webm"
        alt="Year in Motion intro animation"
        caption="Intro animation"
      />
      <Figure
        videoSrc="/videos/yearinmotion_minutes.webm"
        alt="Year in Motion minutes stat"
        caption="Minutes in class animation"
      />
      <Figure
        videoSrc="/videos/yearinmotion_instructors.webm"
        alt="Year in Motion instructors stat"
        caption="Top instructors animation"
      />
      <Figure
        videoSrc="/videos/yearinmotion_outro.webm"
        alt="Year in Motion outro animation"
        caption="Outro animation"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Text block -->
  <div class="content-block-text">
    <p>The experience needed to accommodate a wide range of personalized stats, milestones, and activity patterns while still feeling visually consistent across many fitness brands. Using After Effects and Lottie, I created a flexible motion system that could dynamically inject customer data and brand elements like colors and logos, making the recap feel native to each studio's app.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Two-up images at bottom -->
  <div class="content-block-2up">
    <Figure
      src="/images/yearinmotion_spinco.webp"
      alt="Year in Motion Spinco screens"
      caption="Spinco's branded year in motion screens."
    />
    <Figure
      src="/images/yearinmotion_tremble.webp"
      alt="Year in Motion Tremble screens"
      caption="Tremble's branded year in motion screens."
    />
  </div>
</CaseStudyLayout>
